a:3:{s:11:"notes_total";i:14;s:11:"notes_ctree";a:10:{i:0;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:30;s:5:"title";s:73:"Salesmate upgrades Xero integration; some users may need to re-authorize";s:4:"href";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/salesmate-upgrades-xero-integration-some-users-may-need-to-re-au/";s:13:"href-original";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/salesmate-upgrades-xero-integration-some-users-may-need-to-re-au/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1769173200;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1768047291;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:519:"<p>Salesmate released an upgraded version of its Xero integration and changed the authorization mechanism.</p>
<p>As part of the upgrade, some users may need to complete a one-time re-authorization/migration to avoid sync interruptions.</p>
<p>Recommended action: follow Salesmate’s support documentation and upgrade the Xero integration version.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://www.salesmate.io/blog/january-2026-release-notes/">https://www.salesmate.io/blog/january-2026-release-notes/</a></p>
